# Intelligent Lighting Market Size, Trends & Share Report 2030
## Introduction
The Intelligent Lighting Market Report is segmented by light source, fixture type, control protocol, application, end-user, and geography. The market forecasts are provided in terms of value (USD).

## Market Overview
The intelligent lighting market size stood at USD 5 billion in 2025 and is forecast to reach USD 7.3 billion by 2030, equating to a 7.8% CAGR.

### Key Report Takeaways
* By light source, LED commanded 78% of the intelligent lighting market share in 2024; laser systems are projected to expand at an 18% CAGR from 2025-2030.
* By fixture type, profile types held a 45.72% revenue share in 2024 in the intelligent lighting market, while beam and hybrid lights are advancing at a 12.1% CAGR to 2030.
* By control protocol, DMX-512 held a 54.73% revenue share in 2024 in the intelligent lighting market, while Art-Net / sACN is advancing at a 13% CAGR to 2030.
* By application, indoor venues held a 60% revenue share in 2024 in the intelligent lighting market, while outdoor projects are advancing at a 13% CAGR to 2030.
* By end-user, theatres and concerts accounted for a 41% slice of the intelligent lighting market size in 2024, whereas esports arenas are growing at an 18% CAGR during 2025-2030.
* By geography, Europe led with 33% share of the intelligent lighting market in 2024; APAC is forecast to register the highest regional CAGR at 10% through 2030.

